1
00:00:00,670 --> 00:00:03,170
My name is Antranig Artin Kevorg

2
00:00:03,801 --> 00:00:05,891
I was born in 1941

3
00:00:07,257 --> 00:00:09,829
I was a church official

4
00:00:10,980 --> 00:00:16,393
I worked as a financial accountant in the church

5
00:00:17,094 --> 00:00:19,154
I worked here for twenty-five years

6
00:00:21,590 --> 00:00:27,658
This church was built in 1857 in the old style

7
00:00:30,265 --> 00:00:35,084
Over time, its walls collapsed

8
00:00:35,225 --> 00:00:40,512
Which forced us to rebuild it in 1965

9
00:00:41,559 --> 00:00:45,725
In this church we used to gather the Armenians every Friday

10
00:00:47,798 --> 00:00:52,258
Interviewer: Well, Mr. Abu Mari, regarding the differences

11
00:00:55,652 --> 00:00:59,801
Compared to other churches in Mosul, how was this church different?

12
00:00:59,894 --> 00:01:03,787
This church was different from the other churches...

13
00:01:03,960 --> 00:01:06,521
Different in name only, not in religion

14
00:01:07,658 --> 00:01:12,824
Its name was the Armenian Orthodox Church, while the others

15
00:01:13,492 --> 00:01:16,805
Were named Syriac Catholic or Syriac Orthodox

16
00:01:19,653 --> 00:01:21,710
Or Dominican and other names

17
00:01:21,789 --> 00:01:24,413
But this church was for Armenians, specifically for Armenians

18
00:01:24,873 --> 00:01:32,129
This plaque on the church door was completely defaced

19
00:01:32,857 --> 00:01:43,857
It is written in Armenian—The <i>Surb Etchmiadzin</i> [The Holy Descent of the Only-Begotten] Cathedral was built in 1857 and was renovated in 1965

20
00:01:44,608 --> 00:01:46,674
Armenian Orthodox Church

21
00:01:49,235 --> 00:01:52,207
It means the name of the church is <i>Surb Etchmiadzin</i>

22
00:01:53,725 --> 00:01:55,725
What does this name mean?

23
00:01:57,157 --> 00:02:01,423
In Armenia there is the mother church

24
00:02:02,154 --> 00:02:04,154
It means we belong to it

25
00:02:04,537 --> 00:02:07,283
It means the name <i>Echmiadzin</i> was left here
